# Theming

## Core Rules

- **Never hardcode colors** — always use the theme system
- **Support both light and dark mode** — test in both
- Primary color: **violet** (`#845ef7`)
- Use semantic color references: text, background, primary, border, dimmed

## Mobile (`apps/mobile/`)

Use `useColorScheme` + `Colors` constants + themed components:

```typescript
import { useColorScheme } from '@/hooks/useColorScheme';
import { Colors } from '@/constants/Colors';

const colorScheme = useColorScheme();
const theme = Colors[colorScheme ?? 'light'];

// Semantic usage
color: theme.text              // primary text
backgroundColor: theme.background  // main background
backgroundColor: theme.primary[5]  // primary actions
borderColor: theme.gray[3]    // borders
color: theme.gray[6]          // secondary text
```

Prefer `<ThemedText>` and `<ThemedView>` components over manual styling.

## Web (`apps/web/`)

Use Mantine CSS variables. Prefer CSS vars over `theme.colors.*`:

```css
color: var(--mantine-color-text);
background-color: var(--mantine-color-body);
border-color: var(--mantine-color-border);
color: var(--mantine-color-dimmed);
```

For dark/light differences in CSS:

```css
background-color: light-dark(var(--mantine-color-white), var(--mantine-color-dark-7));
```

Runtime `theme.colors.*` access is acceptable only for dynamic color computation.
